      <body>
         <p>Deism names the rational belief that God has remained distant from Creation, allowing it
            to play out as it will according to certain "natural laws" woven into its very fabric.
            In this view, which was especially prevalent in 18th century England, God neither guides
            nor intervenes in Creation. When applied to the created world, reason alone could
            perfectly deduce God's existence and nature. Indeed, Deists often repudiated the
            Incarnation as supernatural (i.e., irrational) and superfluous to Christianity.</p>
